1
00:01:12,906 --> 00:01:15,033
[Man Narrating]
How I miss Scotland...

2
00:01:15,108 --> 00:01:18,441
and the sea... the sea.

3
00:01:18,511 --> 00:01:21,912
There's nothing like it
in all the Earth...

4
00:01:21,981 --> 00:01:25,041
the salt in your face,
the wind at your back...

5
00:01:25,118 --> 00:01:27,484
and all the world before you.

6
00:01:27,554 --> 00:01:31,615
And you're freer than a bird in the air
or a fish in the ocean.

7
00:01:31,691 --> 00:01:34,455
To be free...

8
00:01:34,527 --> 00:01:38,793
I reckon that's why I joined
the Second War to end all wars.

9
00:01:43,736 --> 00:01:46,227
## [Bagpipes, Drums]

10
00:01:48,708 --> 00:01:53,008
I was at the university studying to be
a teacher when the call to arms occurred.

11
00:01:53,079 --> 00:01:57,038
I was only too eager to put aside my studies
for the glory of action.

12
00:01:57,117 --> 00:02:02,054
I stopped reading history
and became a part of it.

13
00:02:02,122 --> 00:02:05,649
I joined the proud ranks of
the Argyll & Sutherland Highlanders...

14
00:02:05,725 --> 00:02:08,626
and became Captain Ernest Gordon.

15
00:02:10,396 --> 00:02:14,526
My commanding officer was
Lieutenant Colonel Stuart McLean,

16
00:02:14,601 --> 00:02:18,059
the finest commander
the 93rd Battalion ever had,

17
00:02:18,138 --> 00:02:21,403
a man of deep loyalties
to his country,

18
00:02:21,474 --> 00:02:24,910
his duty and his men,

19
00:02:24,978 --> 00:02:28,914
a loyalty that was soon to be matched
by his own second in command,

20
00:02:28,982 --> 00:02:30,973
Major lan Campbell,

21
00:02:31,050 --> 00:02:35,544
a man of passionate devotion to the colonel
as well as the cause.

22
00:02:38,158 --> 00:02:42,185
And it was our loyalties
that would eventually be tested.

23
00:02:42,262 --> 00:02:46,392
The Argylls had a legacy
or being the last line of defense,

24
00:02:48,034 --> 00:02:51,435
and we were to prove
that legacy once again...

25
00:02:51,504 --> 00:02:54,371
in the face of defeat...

26
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:56,601
and capture by the enemy.

27
00:02:59,145 --> 00:03:02,376
[Explosions]

28
00:03:12,325 --> 00:03:15,260
[Man Speaking Japanese]

29
00:03:15,328 --> 00:03:18,320
[Grunting]

30
00:03:32,178 --> 00:03:34,669
[Japanese Continues]

31
00:03:43,756 --> 00:03:47,214
[Prisoners Grunting]

32
00:03:53,066 --> 00:03:55,830
Sir.! Sir.!

33
00:03:55,902 --> 00:03:58,200
You all right, sir?

34
00:03:58,271 --> 00:04:02,401
You look the devil in the face
with pride, boys!

35
00:04:03,977 --> 00:04:06,639
And try not shit your kilts.

36
00:04:06,713 --> 00:04:08,647
[Weapons Cocking]

37
00:04:12,018 --> 00:04:14,612
[Gunfire]

38
00:04:14,687 --> 00:04:17,178
[Laughter]

39
00:04:18,858 --> 00:04:20,985
Bastards are just
playing with our minds.

40
00:04:43,216 --> 00:04:45,480
[Horn Honking]

41
00:04:58,598 --> 00:05:01,294
[Shouting Orders In Japanese]

42
00:05:31,864 --> 00:05:34,264
[Gordon Narrating]
When you surrender in war,

43
00:05:34,334 --> 00:05:36,962
you're stripped of your dignity
as a soldier.

44
00:05:37,036 --> 00:05:40,301
All you've got left
is your fellow comrades,

45
00:05:40,373 --> 00:05:43,467
many of whom you'vejust met.

46
00:05:43,543 --> 00:05:46,376
LieutenantJim Reardon,
merchant marine,

47
00:05:46,446 --> 00:05:48,573
one of the few Americans
in the area.

48
00:05:48,648 --> 00:05:52,243
Attached himself to the Argylls
during the Allied surrender.

49
00:05:52,318 --> 00:05:55,879
We called him 'Yanker,"
'cause he was both an American...

50
00:05:55,955 --> 00:05:59,584
- and a bit of a wanker.
- [Whistle Blows]

51
00:07:02,588 --> 00:07:05,489
[Coughing]

52
00:07:07,393 --> 00:07:10,362
Parade, halt.

53
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:12,489
[Distant Gunfiire]

54
00:07:15,568 --> 00:07:17,559
What's that stench?

55
00:07:19,305 --> 00:07:21,296
That'll be death, Major.

56
00:07:28,247 --> 00:07:30,238
Sir.!

57
00:07:32,652 --> 00:07:35,553
[Grunting, Shouting]

58
00:07:53,506 --> 00:07:57,067
Parade, right wheel.

59
00:08:01,514 --> 00:08:03,948
Parade, halt.

60
00:08:05,017 --> 00:08:07,451
Left turn.

61
00:08:09,021 --> 00:08:11,216
Stand at ease.

62
00:08:15,561 --> 00:08:17,552
Stand easy.

63
00:08:23,135 --> 00:08:25,126
[Japanese]

64
00:08:27,773 --> 00:08:30,674
What the hell
does "tenko" mean?

65
00:08:30,743 --> 00:08:32,904
Must be roll call.

66
00:08:39,185 --> 00:08:42,882
Today, you will
count off in English.

67
00:08:42,955 --> 00:08:46,823
But tomorrow and forever,
in Japanese.

68
00:09:09,682 --> 00:09:13,015
- Start counting!
- One!

69
00:09:13,085 --> 00:09:14,985
- Two!
- Three.!

70
00:09:15,054 --> 00:09:17,147
- Four.!
- Five.

71
00:09:17,223 --> 00:09:19,020
- Six.
- Big-eared Nip.

72
00:09:20,393 --> 00:09:22,327
[Groans]

73
00:09:23,596 --> 00:09:26,258
Bastard.

74
00:09:28,834 --> 00:09:31,496
[Shouts In Japanese]

75
00:09:31,571 --> 00:09:34,665
[Grunting, Groaning]

76
00:09:38,277 --> 00:09:43,476
This is a shame culture.
You make 'em lose face, you'll pay. Stand easy.

77
00:09:46,052 --> 00:09:48,680
[McLean]
This is an outrage.!

78
00:09:48,754 --> 00:09:51,484
I am a senior officer,

79
00:09:51,557 --> 00:09:55,288
and I will not tolerate
this barbaric behavior!

80
00:09:55,361 --> 00:09:58,125
This man has rights!

81
00:10:01,968 --> 00:10:03,799
[Japanese]

82
00:10:11,143 --> 00:10:13,134
Dirty...

83
00:10:24,357 --> 00:10:27,121
[Japanese]

84
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:44,469
Attention, prisoners.
You are now captives...

85
00:10:44,543 --> 00:10:47,910
of His Imperial Majesty,
the emperor.

86
00:10:47,980 --> 00:10:49,914
[Commander, Japanese]

87
00:10:57,456 --> 00:11:02,393
Behold... the extreme penalty
for those who try to escape.

88
00:11:04,497 --> 00:11:06,761
- [Shouts In Japanese]
- [Rifes Fire]

89
00:11:16,375 --> 00:11:19,037
[Commander, Japanese]

90
00:11:26,552 --> 00:11:28,850
This is for your own sake.

91
00:11:30,122 --> 00:11:34,855
You will sign these papers
promising not to escape.

92
00:11:40,966 --> 00:11:44,993
- No escape, my Yankee ass.
- This is against the Geneva Convention.

93
00:11:45,071 --> 00:11:47,938
They don't give two shits
about the Geneva Convention.

94
00:11:48,007 --> 00:11:50,202
[Translator]
Tomorrow,

95
00:11:50,276 --> 00:11:55,009
you will bring these signed papers
from all prisoners.

96
00:11:55,081 --> 00:11:57,413
You are dismissed.

97
00:12:02,822 --> 00:12:05,256
- [Japanese]
- [Gurgling]

98
00:12:26,178 --> 00:12:28,271
[Japanese]

99
00:12:42,595 --> 00:12:45,120
Go. Go!

100
00:13:13,192 --> 00:13:16,457
- What did you just say?
- I told him you were stupid.

101
00:13:17,763 --> 00:13:20,960
Don't know whether
to thank you or kick your ass.

102
00:13:21,033 --> 00:13:23,263
Lan Campbell.

103
00:13:23,335 --> 00:13:25,496
Dusty Miller.

104
00:13:25,571 --> 00:13:27,903
Where'd you learn
to speakJapanese?

105
00:13:29,241 --> 00:13:31,505
What with the colonel?

106
00:13:31,577 --> 00:13:34,512
You want your colonel back?

107
00:13:34,580 --> 00:13:36,741
Owe the man my life.

108
00:13:37,917 --> 00:13:41,614
- The more hair, the more lice.
- Ow!

109
00:13:41,687 --> 00:13:46,454
A word of advice...
stay close to your cobbers.

110
00:13:46,525 --> 00:13:50,052
But when it comes right down to it,
it's survival of the fittest.

111
00:13:50,129 --> 00:13:55,863
Every man for himself.
Barter is the name of the game, gents.

112
00:13:55,935 --> 00:14:00,702
They call the hospital the Death House.
You don't want to end up in here.

113
00:14:02,341 --> 00:14:07,643
Relish your health now, gentlemen.
It's the last you'll see of it.

114
00:14:07,713 --> 00:14:12,309
There are thousands more prisoners
in camps all along the river.

115
00:14:12,384 --> 00:14:15,717
Not too much skinny here
from the outside.

116
00:14:15,788 --> 00:14:18,018
Japs keep us in the dark.

117
00:14:18,090 --> 00:14:20,081
No radios.

118
00:14:20,159 --> 00:14:22,923
They catch one, they'll kill you.

119
00:14:25,064 --> 00:14:29,125
Officers, try to keep
your shirt on.

120
00:14:29,201 --> 00:14:32,068
It'll distinguish you from the grunts,
which is about the only thing...

121
00:14:32,137 --> 00:14:36,506
that's keeping us from degenerating
into a bloody anarchy.

122
00:14:42,214 --> 00:14:44,512
Oh, shit.

123
00:15:05,371 --> 00:15:07,464
Ernie, where ya goin'?

124
00:15:07,539 --> 00:15:10,269
To find out about the colonel.

125
00:15:10,342 --> 00:15:13,106
You're just askin' for trouble!

126
00:15:22,788 --> 00:15:24,779
- [Shouting]
- [Screaming]

127
00:15:38,404 --> 00:15:40,338
Doc.

128
00:15:40,406 --> 00:15:42,340
Get him down here.

129
00:15:42,408 --> 00:15:44,399
[Moaning]

130
00:15:46,078 --> 00:15:48,808
- Come on.
- Easy. Easy.

131
00:15:48,881 --> 00:15:51,372
It's my back.
My back, my back.

132
00:15:51,450 --> 00:15:55,819
- Eh.
- What the bloody hell happened?

133
00:15:55,888 --> 00:15:58,789
- Looks like you didn't bow.
- What?

134
00:15:58,857 --> 00:16:03,191
Always bow before a guard,
Korean orJap.

135
00:16:03,262 --> 00:16:05,924
Never look 'em in the eyes
when they pass you.

136
00:16:05,998 --> 00:16:08,990
That's pure defiance.
Always look away. Rules of Bushido.

137
00:16:09,068 --> 00:16:11,536
- Bushido?
- Their kind of chivalry.

138
00:16:11,603 --> 00:16:14,766
Respect and obligation.

139
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:17,775
If you don't respect them,
they feel obligated to bash you.

140
00:16:17,843 --> 00:16:21,711
- Nothing personal.
- Well, it sure as bloody well feels personal.

141
00:16:21,780 --> 00:16:26,012
Yeah, well, it works both ways.
They do the same to their own.

142
00:16:26,085 --> 00:16:29,179
- That's a comfort.
- Now listen.

143
00:16:29,254 --> 00:16:34,886
You must understand, these monsters truly believe
we're an inferior race... less than human.

144
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:39,556
Now, beating a prisoner to them
is like beating a disobedient dog,

145
00:16:39,631 --> 00:16:43,965
and the fiercer the beating,
the fiercer their dedication to the emperor.

146
00:16:44,036 --> 00:16:46,766
- [Groans]
- You'll be all right, son.

147
00:16:49,641 --> 00:16:51,802
Make space for the colonel.

148
00:16:53,379 --> 00:16:56,041
[Doctor]
You're buggers for punishment, you lot.

149
00:17:05,758 --> 00:17:09,353
- You should've let 'em take me instead, sir.
- [McLean Wheezing]

150
00:17:10,963 --> 00:17:16,663
- Anything we can do for you, Colonel?
- Ah. Start preparing.

151
00:17:16,735 --> 00:17:19,295
Preparing for what?

152
00:17:19,371 --> 00:17:23,330
Escape. Heh!
What else, you towheaded Yank?

153
00:17:25,044 --> 00:17:26,409
Dusty.

154
00:17:28,380 --> 00:17:30,678
Thank you.

155
00:17:38,157 --> 00:17:43,254
Colonel, I've been watching these Nips.
There's never more than a handful of them...

156
00:17:43,328 --> 00:17:47,094
guarding the perimeter at any given time,
and they're not watching very closely.

157
00:17:47,166 --> 00:17:50,397
- Itjust doesn't make sense to me unless...
- Unless what?

158
00:17:50,469 --> 00:17:55,771
Unless every prisoner's been caught or died
in a thousand miles of hostile jungle.

159
00:17:55,841 --> 00:18:00,335
Unless the local villagers are willing
to turn in a P.O.W. For a bowl of rice.

160
00:18:00,412 --> 00:18:03,609
Unless...
Escape is impossible.

161
00:18:04,850 --> 00:18:06,841
Excellent.

162
00:18:07,853 --> 00:18:10,048
Yanker.

163
00:18:10,122 --> 00:18:13,182
You find the best
escape route, hmm?

164
00:18:13,258 --> 00:18:15,488
- Lan.
- Yes, sir.

165
00:18:15,561 --> 00:18:20,328
You should start getting
survival gear together, hmm?

166
00:18:20,399 --> 00:18:24,062
Ernest, get things together.

167
00:18:24,136 --> 00:18:27,299
- We can trade with the locals.
- Yes, sir.

168
00:18:27,372 --> 00:18:31,138
And as soon as I'm well,
we're on our way.

169
00:18:31,210 --> 00:18:33,872
- Yes, sir. Yes, sir.
- Okay?

170
00:18:33,946 --> 00:18:35,413
- Good.
- Sir.

171
00:18:35,481 --> 00:18:38,006
Good boys.

172
00:18:38,083 --> 00:18:40,017
They're good boys.

173
00:18:40,085 --> 00:18:42,076
That's my boys.

174
00:19:01,840 --> 00:19:05,241
Hey. How about some extra
for my colonel?

175
00:19:05,310 --> 00:19:09,610
- He's in the Death House.
- If your colonel can't make it,
it means he can't work.

176
00:19:09,681 --> 00:19:12,707
If he can't work, he can't eat.
Nip rules. Move along.

177
00:19:13,785 --> 00:19:15,912
Come on, pal.
I'll owe you one.

178
00:19:15,988 --> 00:19:18,047
Hey, you heard him.
He said, move along!

179
00:19:18,123 --> 00:19:21,820
- [Crowd Goading]
- You look like a sheep-humping highlander!

180
00:19:23,195 --> 00:19:24,924
Come on!

181
00:19:34,173 --> 00:19:35,765
- Yeah!
- Do it!

182
00:19:37,476 --> 00:19:41,606
What are you, bloody chicken?
I'll kick your ass.!

183
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:45,207
Come on, you English fuck!

184
00:19:48,086 --> 00:19:50,247
Well, come on, then, wanker.!

185
00:19:52,824 --> 00:19:55,088
Well, come on!

186
00:19:58,363 --> 00:20:00,763
It's enough.

187
00:20:00,832 --> 00:20:03,596
[Gordon Narrating]
What does it take for a man to lose his dignity?

188
00:20:08,874 --> 00:20:11,138
Come on, you English fuck.!

189
00:20:11,210 --> 00:20:15,943
How far can he fall
to pay the price of survival?

190
00:20:19,284 --> 00:20:21,275
- [Grunts]
- [Bowl Clatters]

191
00:20:39,471 --> 00:20:44,636
Dusty built a sanctuaryjust outside the camp
called the Church Without Walls.

192
00:20:44,710 --> 00:20:47,372
We were allowed
to visit it freely.

193
00:20:47,446 --> 00:20:49,744
They knew we had
nowhere to go.

194
00:21:10,936 --> 00:21:14,872
[Campbell] I'll tell you what I'm gonna do
soon as I get back to Glasgow.

195
00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:18,205
Gonna visit my favorite pub.

196
00:21:18,277 --> 00:21:22,236
- I'm gonna sink... 14 whiskeys and seven pints.
- [Ticking]

197
00:21:26,852 --> 00:21:30,379
And I'm gonna spend the night in the arms
of my tender, lovin' wee wife.

198
00:21:30,455 --> 00:21:33,583
- You're married, sir?
- No, but if you got a sister, I'm available.

199
00:21:36,161 --> 00:21:38,857
What about you, Ernie?

200
00:21:40,332 --> 00:21:42,323
Probably teach.

201
00:21:44,936 --> 00:21:46,927
I've always fancied teaching.

202
00:21:49,741 --> 00:21:52,073
I thought I'd see
the world first though.

203
00:21:52,144 --> 00:21:55,807
- You got that wish.
- Aye.

204
00:21:58,417 --> 00:22:03,116
When I get outta here, I'm gonna go into
business for myself and get stinkin' rich.

205
00:22:03,188 --> 00:22:05,622
What kind of business?

206
00:22:05,691 --> 00:22:08,251
Black market. Prostitution.

207
00:22:08,327 --> 00:22:12,229
I'll tell ya what, mate. You're not gonna make
much money as a prostitute, I'll tell you that.

208
00:22:14,533 --> 00:22:16,524
What about you, sir?

209
00:22:18,637 --> 00:22:20,867
What are you gonna do
after the war?

210
00:22:22,674 --> 00:22:25,370
Start preparing for the next war.

211
00:22:35,320 --> 00:22:37,311
[Guards Shouting]

212
00:22:50,602 --> 00:22:53,833
[Gordon Narrating]
In the Bushido code, the nation is everything.

213
00:22:53,905 --> 00:22:55,896
The individual is nothing.

214
00:22:55,974 --> 00:22:59,137
Conformity is how they gain
their sense of purpose,

215
00:22:59,211 --> 00:23:01,941
and they expected us
to fall in line as well.

216
00:23:03,148 --> 00:23:05,742
[Japanese]

217
00:23:08,820 --> 00:23:11,414
[All Repeating]

218
00:23:16,695 --> 00:23:18,856
What are we saying, Dusty?

219
00:23:18,930 --> 00:23:23,629
Loyalty, politeness, frugality.
Soldier's duty.

220
00:23:23,702 --> 00:23:25,966
Well, isn't that just dandy.

221
00:23:54,366 --> 00:23:56,766
[Shouting]

222
00:23:58,303 --> 00:24:00,635
Carry on, Sergeant Major.

223
00:24:00,705 --> 00:24:03,765
Parade! Parade-tion!

224
00:24:05,010 --> 00:24:07,069
About face.

225
00:24:46,117 --> 00:24:50,713
[Translator] All show respect for
honorable Lieutenant Colonel Nagatomo,

226
00:24:50,789 --> 00:24:54,919
- Chief ofThailand P.O.W. Administration.
- [Shouts]

227
00:25:12,110 --> 00:25:14,271
I think she fancies me.

228
00:25:25,056 --> 00:25:28,492
It is great pleasure for me...

229
00:25:28,560 --> 00:25:32,553
to see you at this place.

230
00:25:32,631 --> 00:25:35,065
You are few
remaining skeleton...

231
00:25:35,133 --> 00:25:38,933
of our victory
and our pitiful victim.

232
00:25:39,004 --> 00:25:42,132
You should weep
with gratitude...

233
00:25:42,207 --> 00:25:46,166
at His Imperial Majesty,
the emperor,

234
00:25:46,244 --> 00:25:49,008
who pity you
for being coward!

235
00:25:51,249 --> 00:25:54,377
- What's he talking about, cowards?
- Rules of Bushido.

236
00:25:54,452 --> 00:25:58,115
They believe the losers
should kill themselves.

237
00:25:58,189 --> 00:26:01,352
You will give me
great pleasure...

238
00:26:01,426 --> 00:26:04,327
to build a railroad...

239
00:26:04,396 --> 00:26:08,833
through the jungle to the glory
of His Imperial Majesty,

240
00:26:08,900 --> 00:26:11,061
the emperor,

241
00:26:11,136 --> 00:26:14,037
saviour ofJapan!

242
00:26:14,105 --> 00:26:16,096
Saviour of Asia!

243
00:26:18,076 --> 00:26:21,978
We will build this railroad...

244
00:26:22,047 --> 00:26:27,280
if we have to build it
over the white man's body.

245
00:26:29,554 --> 00:26:32,887
It is your purification.

246
00:26:44,603 --> 00:26:46,594
[Japanese]

247
00:26:52,744 --> 00:26:54,735
Hmm.
[Japanese]

248
00:27:09,828 --> 00:27:14,094
Railroad to be 420 kilometer,

249
00:27:14,165 --> 00:27:17,100
from Chungkai base camp to...

250
00:27:17,168 --> 00:27:19,159
Thanbyuzayat in north.

251
00:27:21,473 --> 00:27:25,409
[Japanese]

252
00:27:28,246 --> 00:27:31,079
You will build the railroad
in 18 months.

253
00:27:31,149 --> 00:27:33,140
Eighteen months?

254
00:27:34,786 --> 00:27:39,189
How will my men manage that on
the rations you're feeding them, hmm?

255
00:27:39,257 --> 00:27:41,248
[Japanese]

256
00:27:46,064 --> 00:27:48,396
Officers work as well.

257
00:27:49,534 --> 00:27:51,798
[Japanese]

258
00:27:55,807 --> 00:27:59,072
Royal engineer
will oversee building.

259
00:28:06,418 --> 00:28:08,886
Where are the signed papers?

260
00:28:10,588 --> 00:28:12,579
Gentlemen,

261
00:28:13,758 --> 00:28:17,717
as you have violated
the Geneva Convention,

262
00:28:17,796 --> 00:28:21,459
the Hague Convention...

263
00:28:21,533 --> 00:28:26,800
and every human right
for properly supervised prisoners of war,

264
00:28:26,871 --> 00:28:29,305
may I respectfully recommend...

265
00:28:29,374 --> 00:28:31,467
that you...

266
00:28:31,543 --> 00:28:34,876
and your fascist monkeys...

267
00:28:34,946 --> 00:28:37,471
stick your head
up your ass.!

268
00:28:37,549 --> 00:28:42,418
Because we will not sign
your bloody paper!

269
00:28:42,487 --> 00:28:45,183
Now translate that!

270
00:28:45,256 --> 00:28:47,588
[Translating]

271
00:28:51,029 --> 00:28:54,863
I am sick of this drivel!

272
00:28:59,003 --> 00:29:00,994
- Gentlemen.
- Sir.

273
00:29:02,040 --> 00:29:04,133
[Shouts]

274
00:29:11,049 --> 00:29:13,040
[Japanese]

275
00:29:18,857 --> 00:29:20,848
Look after my boys, lan.

276
00:29:25,730 --> 00:29:28,358
It is regrettable, but...

277
00:29:28,433 --> 00:29:32,301
we take each of you
and shoot one by one.!

278
00:29:32,370 --> 00:29:35,339
- [Doctor] Come on, man.
- Sir!

279
00:29:35,406 --> 00:29:38,842
Until you respect Emperor!

280
00:29:38,910 --> 00:29:41,003
Come on. Out of here.
Out of here!

281
00:29:41,079 --> 00:29:43,377
- Fuck! Fuck him!
- Come on! Come on, man! Come on!

282
00:29:43,448 --> 00:29:46,212
- Fuck.!
- Come on, man.! Out ofhere.!

283
00:29:46,284 --> 00:29:48,980
- Bastard! Fucking bastard!
- Out, out of here!

284
00:29:54,125 --> 00:29:56,525
- Fucking...
- Come.

285
00:29:56,594 --> 00:30:00,030
- Major, what happened? What happened?
- Fucking shot!

286
00:30:00,098 --> 00:30:04,159
- Where's the...
- Fucking... Fucking shot!

287
00:30:04,235 --> 00:30:07,102
It's the colonel's blood.
It's the colonel's blood!

288
00:30:07,172 --> 00:30:09,197
[Overlapping Shouts]

289
00:30:09,274 --> 00:30:12,437
Fucking shot him.!

290
00:30:12,510 --> 00:30:14,671
- The bastard!
- [Reardon] Major.

291
00:30:14,746 --> 00:30:16,976
Major, the colonel!

292
00:30:28,626 --> 00:30:30,856
[Moaning]

293
00:31:12,470 --> 00:31:15,837
You fucking slanted-eyed...

294
00:31:15,907 --> 00:31:18,341
- Don't let him go!
- Campbell!

295
00:31:19,477 --> 00:31:21,945
Don't be another!
Enough is enough!

296
00:31:23,815 --> 00:31:26,306
[Overlapping Shouts]

297
00:31:27,318 --> 00:31:29,445
Fucking bastard.!

298
00:31:29,520 --> 00:31:32,512
[No Audible Dialogue]

299
00:31:51,843 --> 00:31:53,834
[Japanese]

300
00:31:55,513 --> 00:31:57,981
There's nothing you can do.
There's nothing you can do.

301
00:31:58,049 --> 00:32:00,040
How can he die?

302
00:32:01,519 --> 00:32:03,612
- What are we gonna do?
- It's all right.

303
00:32:03,688 --> 00:32:06,122
- What the fuck are we gonna do now?
- Shh!

304
00:32:06,190 --> 00:32:08,954
What the fuck
are we gonna do now?

305
00:32:09,027 --> 00:32:11,188
[Gordon]
Just stay down, Major.

306
00:32:13,564 --> 00:32:15,930
"Verily, verily, I say unto you,

307
00:32:18,102 --> 00:32:21,196
"except a corn of wheat
fall into the ground and die,

308
00:32:22,473 --> 00:32:24,464
'it abideth alone.

309
00:32:25,543 --> 00:32:27,534
"But if it die,

310
00:32:27,612 --> 00:32:30,240
it bringeth forth much fruit."

311
00:32:36,721 --> 00:32:38,916
There is suffering before glory.

312
00:32:43,227 --> 00:32:45,593
There is a cross...

313
00:32:45,663 --> 00:32:47,858
before the crown.

314
00:32:51,469 --> 00:32:53,903
## ["Amazing Grace"]

315
00:33:04,949 --> 00:33:07,611
Outward, turn!

316
00:33:10,722 --> 00:33:13,555
Slow, march.!

317
00:34:00,772 --> 00:34:03,536
- Cheers.
- I'm not leaving.

318
00:34:07,078 --> 00:34:09,774
What?

319
00:34:09,847 --> 00:34:12,611
I said, I'm not leaving.

320
00:34:12,683 --> 00:34:14,674
What about our plan?

321
00:34:17,155 --> 00:34:19,487
I owed the colonel my life.

322
00:34:21,292 --> 00:34:25,991
And I watched him die in front of my eyes,
and I just stood there doing nothing.

323
00:34:27,165 --> 00:34:30,225
You think you're
the only one suffering here?

324
00:34:30,301 --> 00:34:33,998
- You think you're the only one...
- Now waken up!

325
00:34:34,072 --> 00:34:36,404
There's a reason why
every escape has failed,

326
00:34:36,474 --> 00:34:40,342
and there's a reason why theJaps
don't give a toss about security.

327
00:34:43,314 --> 00:34:46,078
We were fools to think
we even stood a chance.

328
00:34:50,054 --> 00:34:52,284
I've got my own plans now.

329
00:34:55,726 --> 00:34:58,559
You are a selfish bastard.

330
00:35:00,898 --> 00:35:02,832
Come on, Ernie.

331
00:35:05,736 --> 00:35:08,000
Ernie!

332
00:35:13,511 --> 00:35:15,502
Fine!

333
00:35:15,580 --> 00:35:18,242
[Gordon]
Yanker, wait a minute.!

334
00:35:19,250 --> 00:35:21,184
Yanker, wait!

335
00:35:21,252 --> 00:35:24,187
You'll never make it on your own
in that jungle. It's suicide!

336
00:35:24,255 --> 00:35:28,316
Take a look around you!
Take a look in the eyes of these men.

337
00:35:28,392 --> 00:35:30,690
You tell me what you see.

338
00:35:30,761 --> 00:35:33,093
That's right, Ernie.
They're dead already.

339
00:35:33,164 --> 00:35:35,496
You know it, and I know it.

340
00:35:35,566 --> 00:35:38,228
Everybody in there does, too,
except they're afraid to admit the obvious,

341
00:35:38,302 --> 00:35:41,567
and that scares
the fuckin' hell out of me!

342
00:35:41,639 --> 00:35:44,107
Because at least with escape...

343
00:35:44,175 --> 00:35:48,578
it gave us one thing... hope.

344
00:35:48,646 --> 00:35:52,343
Hope, Ernie. Because without that,
we might as well be sitting in there...

345
00:35:52,416 --> 00:35:54,782
with our thumbs up our asses
waitin' for the end to come!

346
00:35:54,852 --> 00:35:57,844
Is that what you want?

347
00:35:58,890 --> 00:36:01,620
Let me tell you
something about me.

348
00:36:01,692 --> 00:36:04,923
I am not a stupid man,

349
00:36:04,996 --> 00:36:08,261
and I am not a kamikaze.

350
00:36:08,332 --> 00:36:12,029
If I can't escape,
I'll do the next best thing.

351
00:36:12,103 --> 00:36:14,230
I will take care of myself.

352
00:36:14,305 --> 00:36:17,069
And that's exactly
what I plan on doing.

353
00:36:17,141 --> 00:36:21,237
Yanker! We are all in this,
all of us together!

354
00:36:21,312 --> 00:36:24,941
Sure, kid.
Every single one of us.

355
00:36:41,999 --> 00:36:43,967
[Camera Shutter Clicking]

356
00:36:44,035 --> 00:36:47,266
[Gordon Narrating]
TheJapanese were preparing to invade India.

357
00:36:47,338 --> 00:36:50,398
The railway would be
their supply line.

358
00:36:50,474 --> 00:36:52,465
We would be
the means to their end.

359
00:36:55,079 --> 00:36:57,741
[Shouting In Japanese]

360
00:37:10,161 --> 00:37:13,528
When you're living to die,
every minute is an eternity.

361
00:37:15,066 --> 00:37:17,091
Days are lost.

362
00:37:17,168 --> 00:37:19,636
Months blend into one another.

363
00:37:19,704 --> 00:37:22,571
And the only reality you know
is in the moment,

364
00:37:23,741 --> 00:37:26,904
and the moment hangs over
you like death.

365
00:37:26,978 --> 00:37:31,608
It's difficult to describe what it's like
to live with permanent hunger in your belly,

366
00:37:31,682 --> 00:37:35,812
and the stench of disease and death
all around you with every breath you take.

367
00:37:35,886 --> 00:37:38,719
Malaria, diphtheria,

368
00:37:38,789 --> 00:37:41,417
pellagra, dysentery...

369
00:37:41,492 --> 00:37:44,825
sucks every ounce offluid
right out of your body.

370
00:37:44,895 --> 00:37:48,797
Your muscles cramp up
and your circulation collapses.

371
00:37:48,866 --> 00:37:52,461
Major! He's burning up.

372
00:37:52,536 --> 00:37:54,663
- Ernie.
- [Gordon Muttering]

373
00:38:00,878 --> 00:38:03,540
[Doctor] I don't know anybody
who could survive that lot.

374
00:38:13,157 --> 00:38:15,148
Oh, Ernie, son.

375
00:38:17,762 --> 00:38:19,923
You are a good soldier...

376
00:38:21,666 --> 00:38:23,657
and a good friend.

377
00:38:38,182 --> 00:38:41,583
[Thinking]
So this is death.

378
00:38:41,652 --> 00:38:44,485
Dark.

379
00:38:44,555 --> 00:38:48,218
Cold. All alone.

380
00:38:50,795 --> 00:38:53,457
No more reason to fight,

381
00:38:53,531 --> 00:38:56,193
so they give up on you.

382
00:38:56,267 --> 00:38:59,361
In death there is
no second chance.

383
00:39:00,638 --> 00:39:03,607
So that's what you think about
when you're dying...

384
00:39:03,674 --> 00:39:07,770
the real value of all that
you've done with your life,

385
00:39:07,845 --> 00:39:10,814
and all that you
might have done...

386
00:39:10,881 --> 00:39:13,372
if only you'd had
a second chance.

387
00:39:27,665 --> 00:39:30,065
[Gasping]

388
00:39:43,414 --> 00:39:46,542
Aah!
[Screams]

389
00:39:56,360 --> 00:40:02,162
Bloody hell! These Nip bastards
are eatin' like the Prince of Wales!

390
00:40:02,233 --> 00:40:04,224
[All Grunting]

391
00:40:07,505 --> 00:40:09,996
[Gordon Narrating]
Life doesn't wait for the individual,

392
00:40:10,074 --> 00:40:12,508
especially life
as a prisoner of war.

393
00:40:17,281 --> 00:40:21,081
If you want to survive,
you need a bit ofluck,

394
00:40:21,152 --> 00:40:25,213
a quick wit and a mate to pick you
up when you fall.

395
00:40:35,232 --> 00:40:38,793
Where am I?

396
00:40:38,869 --> 00:40:41,394
You've been unconscious for days.

397
00:40:44,975 --> 00:40:47,910
I thought if I could get you out of
the Death House and into some fresh air,

398
00:40:47,978 --> 00:40:50,208
you'd have a better
chance of surviving.

399
00:40:50,281 --> 00:40:53,307
Well, I don't know if
I want to survive anymore.

400
00:40:57,621 --> 00:41:02,581
- Open up.
- How did you get the food away from the line?

401
00:41:02,660 --> 00:41:05,424
I have my connections.
Come on. Open up.

402
00:41:05,496 --> 00:41:08,659
Why are you doing this?

403
00:41:16,807 --> 00:41:18,741
Hey, Ernie.

404
00:41:22,813 --> 00:41:27,876
Uh, me and the cobbers,
we've been chewing it over,

405
00:41:28,886 --> 00:41:31,787
and, uh, we got thinking.

406
00:41:34,225 --> 00:41:36,455
What's the purpose
in what we been suffering?

407
00:41:36,527 --> 00:41:39,690
I mean, where's thejustice in...

408
00:41:39,763 --> 00:41:42,857
in Nips bashing us
and working us to death?

409
00:41:42,933 --> 00:41:46,699
And what's worse,
we're killing each other to save our own skins.

410
00:41:48,038 --> 00:41:50,563
What exactly
are you asking me?

411
00:41:50,641 --> 00:41:53,303
You said you wanted
to be a teacher.

412
00:41:53,377 --> 00:41:55,538
Yeah.

413
00:41:55,613 --> 00:41:59,709
We thought that you might have
some answers, sir.

414
00:41:59,783 --> 00:42:02,946
Would you like me to...

415
00:42:03,020 --> 00:42:05,386
take a lecture
on the meaning of life?

416
00:42:05,456 --> 00:42:08,983
Oh, that's
a bloody fine idea, sir!

417
00:42:11,195 --> 00:42:13,186
Please,

418
00:42:14,932 --> 00:42:16,923
just leave me alone.

419
00:42:18,569 --> 00:42:20,799
That's what I figured.

420
00:42:30,414 --> 00:42:35,181
You know, a man can experience an incredible
amount of pain and suffering if he has hope.

421
00:42:38,355 --> 00:42:40,516
When he loses his hope,

422
00:42:42,192 --> 00:42:44,183
that's when he dies.

423
00:43:03,013 --> 00:43:05,345
All right. Uuh.

424
00:43:05,416 --> 00:43:07,577
Shit, I gotta take a shit.

425
00:43:17,127 --> 00:43:19,118
Come on.

426
00:43:19,196 --> 00:43:23,064
[Gordon Narrating] Reardon managed to make
a connection to the local Thai black market.

427
00:43:23,133 --> 00:43:26,000
- Lemme see. Get outta here!
- He wouldn't share it with the others...

428
00:43:26,070 --> 00:43:28,197
for fear ofbeing
discovered by the Nips.

429
00:43:28,272 --> 00:43:31,241
At least, that's what he told us.

430
00:43:33,277 --> 00:43:35,609
[Indistinct Shouts]

431
00:43:40,417 --> 00:43:44,581
Good God, Yanker, that's stinking.!

432
00:43:44,655 --> 00:43:47,180
Right there, Major Campbell,

433
00:43:47,257 --> 00:43:49,418
this is the scent of happiness.

434
00:43:49,493 --> 00:43:53,554
Nectar of the gods.
Our ticket to numbness.

435
00:43:55,032 --> 00:43:59,332
Fermented rice alcohol.
This one's on the house.

436
00:44:08,846 --> 00:44:10,780
[Groans]

437
00:44:10,848 --> 00:44:13,681
- Yeah?
- [Laughing]

438
00:44:14,685 --> 00:44:16,676
Bastard.

439
00:44:18,322 --> 00:44:20,256
He's done it.

440
00:44:20,324 --> 00:44:22,349
Course I've done it.

441
00:44:22,426 --> 00:44:25,361
Oh, nice one, Yanker.
Let's have a swig.

442
00:44:25,429 --> 00:44:27,454
Whoa, whoa, gentlemen.

443
00:44:27,531 --> 00:44:30,364
You want charity, go to church.

444
00:44:30,434 --> 00:44:32,527
As for me, I'm bartering
my way to happiness.

445
00:44:32,603 --> 00:44:34,935
So pony up with some cash.
Anything you got.

446
00:44:35,005 --> 00:44:37,667
Don't be shy.
Line starts right here.

447
00:44:39,009 --> 00:44:40,567
Two cigarettes.

448
00:44:45,182 --> 00:44:48,174
[Grunts]
You've gotta get out of this rain.

449
00:44:49,553 --> 00:44:51,544
Come on. Walk!

450
00:44:51,622 --> 00:44:54,056
- [Gordon Panting]
- Ernie, you bastard!

451
00:44:54,124 --> 00:44:56,592
- You're still alive.!
- Hey, Lazarus!

452
00:44:56,660 --> 00:44:59,652
- Back from the dead, my son.
- Well, I kinda wish I'd stayed there, sir.

453
00:44:59,730 --> 00:45:03,894
Bollocks, soldier.
We need you alive. Hey!

454
00:45:03,967 --> 00:45:06,299
- Come on.
- What's wrong?

455
00:45:07,404 --> 00:45:09,395
He hasn't eaten.

456
00:45:11,675 --> 00:45:14,075
He's been able
to get me extra rations.

457
00:45:14,144 --> 00:45:18,171
He never got you extra rations, Ernie.
He was giving you his.

458
00:45:18,248 --> 00:45:20,478
Help me with his legs.

459
00:45:42,272 --> 00:45:45,639
[Gordon Narrating] I learned that
while Dusty was taking care of me,

460
00:45:45,709 --> 00:45:48,473
the major was preparing
his own plans.

461
00:45:48,545 --> 00:45:50,740
Just what,

462
00:45:50,814 --> 00:45:52,805
I couldn't tell.

463
00:46:03,360 --> 00:46:05,351
[Coughing]

464
00:46:18,408 --> 00:46:20,740
No, no.

465
00:46:20,811 --> 00:46:23,279
Where did you get the food?

466
00:46:23,347 --> 00:46:25,611
Multiple anonymous donors.

467
00:46:25,682 --> 00:46:27,673
Eat.

468
00:46:39,496 --> 00:46:42,522
I've decided to start school
for the jocks.

469
00:46:43,967 --> 00:46:45,958
Ajungle university.

470
00:46:47,337 --> 00:46:49,931
I already made
my own blackboard.

471
00:46:50,007 --> 00:46:52,703
Yanker rustled me up
a textbook,

472
00:46:52,776 --> 00:46:54,937
for no small price.

473
00:46:55,012 --> 00:46:57,810
First class is this evening.

474
00:46:57,881 --> 00:47:00,111
I've got six students already.

475
00:47:01,451 --> 00:47:04,545
I know it's small, but, em,

476
00:47:04,621 --> 00:47:06,612
it's a start.

477
00:47:09,326 --> 00:47:11,658
I don't want to be
the skeptic here, Ernie,

478
00:47:11,728 --> 00:47:15,289
but how in the hell do you expect
to engage in a group activity...

479
00:47:15,365 --> 00:47:17,356
without the Nips seeing you?

480
00:47:17,434 --> 00:47:22,201
In the one place that the Nips
will never go near.

481
00:47:32,549 --> 00:47:36,485
- This stench is intolerable.
- Shut your cake hole!

482
00:47:36,553 --> 00:47:39,716
We're doing the best we can.
Get used to it!

483
00:47:39,790 --> 00:47:43,157
Right, lads.
Eh, make yourself as comfortable as you can,

484
00:47:44,661 --> 00:47:47,129
and let's get started, eh?

485
00:47:51,702 --> 00:47:55,502
I'd like to speak to you about Plato.
[Chuckles]

486
00:47:55,572 --> 00:47:57,597
Um...

487
00:47:57,674 --> 00:47:59,733
All right.

488
00:47:59,810 --> 00:48:01,641
What...

489
00:48:05,282 --> 00:48:07,648
is justice?

490
00:48:09,786 --> 00:48:11,777
[Indistinct Shout]

491
00:48:31,341 --> 00:48:33,502
Excuse me, sir. Sir.

492
00:48:35,279 --> 00:48:38,442
- Is it true you're giving educational classes?
- Mm-hmm.

493
00:48:38,515 --> 00:48:41,882
We'd like to help teach.

494
00:48:41,952 --> 00:48:44,045
Well, what's your story?

495
00:48:44,121 --> 00:48:46,817
Roger Primrose,
trained in the fine arts.

496
00:48:46,890 --> 00:48:49,882
Lieutenant Foxworth here
used to teach Shakespeare at Cambridge.

497
00:48:49,960 --> 00:48:52,292
I'm his platoon sergeant.

498
00:48:52,362 --> 00:48:56,196
Poor blighter's at a loss
without his books and the Bard.

499
00:48:57,701 --> 00:49:00,135
I figure if I can
keep him busy long enough,

500
00:49:00,203 --> 00:49:02,569
he won't end up killing himself.

501
00:49:04,608 --> 00:49:08,237
I'm... not joking, sir.

502
00:49:08,312 --> 00:49:11,543
Well, unfortunately,
we don't have any Shakespeare.

503
00:49:13,383 --> 00:49:16,409
To die, to sleep...

504
