on a pole for all to see.

540
00:51:39,463 --> 00:51:41,454
Any questions?

541
00:51:49,372 --> 00:51:51,397
I've got a question.

542
00:51:54,778 --> 00:51:56,905
- Do you mind?
- Sure.

543
00:51:59,816 --> 00:52:01,807
My question:

544
00:52:01,885 --> 00:52:04,149
If the just man...

545
00:52:04,221 --> 00:52:06,382
is treated as you say,

546
00:52:07,991 --> 00:52:10,687
then what's the just response?

547
00:52:13,263 --> 00:52:16,994
Roll over and let evil
have its wicked way?

548
00:52:17,067 --> 00:52:19,900
Well, what would
you recommend, Major?

549
00:52:19,970 --> 00:52:22,370
Oh, I'd recommend defiance.

550
00:52:22,439 --> 00:52:24,430
Justice for the captors.

551
00:52:24,508 --> 00:52:26,874
An eye for an eye.

552
00:52:26,943 --> 00:52:29,639
- At what price mercy?
- [Chuckles]

553
00:52:32,015 --> 00:52:34,483
Yeah, mercy.

554
00:52:34,551 --> 00:52:36,917
The last bastion
of traitors and cowards.

555
00:52:39,256 --> 00:52:43,750
So you would take a man
and crucify him on a pole for all to see?

556
00:52:46,062 --> 00:52:49,793
